What is Military GPS (M-Code) Receiver Module?
Military GPS (M-Code) receiver modules are advanced navigation components designed to provide highly secure, anti-jam, and encrypted positioning signals for defense platforms. These modules enable enhanced operational resilience because the modernized M-Code signal offers improved resistance to spoofing and interference compared to legacy P(Y)-code systems. They are integrated into a wide range of military assets, including guided munitions, unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), ground vehicles, and next-generation communication systems, ensuring reliability in contested environments.

